Title : OpenID Connect
Text : {{Distinguish|OpenID}}

'''OpenID Connect''' ('''OIDC''') is an [[authentication]] layer on top of [[OAuth#OAuth 2.0|OAuth 2.0]], an [[authorization]] framework.<ref name="//openid.net/connect">{{cite web|title=OpenID Connect|url=https://openid.net/connect/|publisher=OpenID Foundation|accessdate=2016-04-18|language=en}}</ref> The standard is controlled by the [[OpenID#OpenID_Foundation|OpenID Foundation]].

== Description ==

OpenID Connect is a simple identity layer on top of the [[OAuth#OAuth 2.0|OAuth 2.0]] protocol, which allows [[Client (computing)|computing clients]] to verify the identity of an end-user based on the authentication performed by an authorization server, as well as to obtain basic profile information about the end-user in an interoperable and [[REST]]-like manner. In technical terms, OpenID Connect specifies a [[RESTful]] [[HTTP]] [[API]], using [[JSON]] as a data format.

OpenID Connect allows a range of clients, including Web-based, mobile, and [[JavaScript engine|JavaScript]] clients, to request and receive information about authenticated sessions and end-users. The specification suite is [[Extensibility|extensible]], supporting optional features such as encryption of identity data, discovery of OpenID Providers, and session management.<ref name="//openid.net/connect" />

== Open Source Providers ==

There are several [[Open Source]] implementations of OpenID connect providers, including:
* [[MITREid Connect]] from MIT<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://github.com/mitreid-connect/OpenID-Connect-Java-Spring-Server|title=An OpenID Connect reference implementation in Java on the Spring platform.: mitreid-connect/OpenID-Connect-Java-Spring-Server|date=July 2, 2019|via=GitHub}}</ref>
* [[Dex Identity Provider]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://github.com/dexidp/dex|title=OpenID Connect Identity (OIDC) and OAuth 2.0 Provider with Pluggable Connectors: dexidp/dex|date=July 5, 2019|via=GitHub}}</ref>
* [[Ipsilon (service provider)|Ipsilon]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ipsilon-project.org/|title=Ipsilon|website=ipsilon-project.org}}</ref>
* [[IdentityServer4]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://docs.identityserver.io/en/latest/|title=IdentityServer4|date=July 18, 2019}}</ref>

